<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-55-0681 </DOCNO><TEXT>Thoracic disc herniation has been difficult to diagnose, both on clinicalgrounds and by conventional radiologic methods. This entity may masqueradeas a neoplastic mass, particularly if there is a history of primary malignancy.Magnetic resonance imaging was able to establish the correct diagnosisin each of the four cases presented here.</TEXT></DOC>